description:
Create TypeScript type definitions for the core data model.

## Story Context
- **Story:** Data Foundation
- **Purpose:** Users' host entries are represented as typed data structures with validation
- **Contributes To:** Exit state #3 (data persistence), #5 (validation enforced)
- **Unlocks:** All other stories (nothing can be built without the data model)

## Requirements
Define types in src/domain/types.ts:

```typescript
// Entry: represents a single host entry
type Entry = {
  id: string;           // ULID
  ip: string;           // IPv4 or IPv6
  hostname: string;     // RFC 952/1123 compliant
  aliases: string[];    // Additional names
  enabled: boolean;     // Whether this entry is active
  comment?: string;     // Optional user note
};

// Group: hierarchical organization
type Group = {
  name: string;         // Kebab-case identifier
  entries: Entry[];     // Direct children
  groups: Group[];      // Nested groups
};

// HostsFile: root structure
type HostsFile = {
  version: number;      // Schema version (1 for now)
  groups: Group[];      // Top-level groups
};
```

## Files
- src/domain/types.ts (create)

## Verification
- Types compile without errors
- All fields have correct types
- Export all types for use in other modules
